  "prompt": "What should a new team member on development team be assigned to?",
  "response": "When a new team member joins a development team, here are some recommended initial assignments:\n\n1. Getting Started Tasks\n- Documentation review\n- Environment setup\n- Onboarding training\n- Understanding team processes and workflows\n\n2. Low-Risk, Small-Scale Tasks\n- Bug fixes\n- Minor feature improvements\n- Code refactoring\n- Documentation updates\n\n3. Learning-Focused Activities\n- Code reviews\n- Pair programming with experienced team members\n- Working on non-critical components\n- Contributing to test cases\n\n4. Specific Recommendations\n- Start with tasks in familiar technologies\n- Choose tasks with clear requirements\n- Provide tasks that allow gradual complexity increase\n- Assign mentor or buddy for guidance\n\n5. Initial Project Involvement\n- Understand existing codebase\n- Learn team's coding standards\n- Familiarize with development tools\n- Participate in sprint planning/retrospectives\n\n6. Skill Development\n- Work on tasks matching their skill level\n- Gradually increase task complexity\n- Encourage learning and growth\n- Provide constructive feedback\n\nThe goal is to help the new team member integrate smoothly, build confidence, and progressively contribute to the team's objectives.",
